1119
01:32:14,920 --> 01:32:20,040
First question, what are two or three books 
that you've recommended most to other people?

1120
01:32:20,040 --> 01:32:23,080
Few I've recommended most of them are 
Over My Shoulder, actually Range by  

1121
01:32:23,080 --> 01:32:27,920
David Epstein. I think are really critical PM 
work really being able to be a master of a lot  

1122
01:32:27,920 --> 01:32:33,280
of different things or somewhat deep in a lot 
of different things. Deep Work, Cal Newport,  

1123
01:32:33,280 --> 01:32:37,280
kind of clearing space to be focused and do 
the things thinking about the most important  

1124
01:32:37,280 --> 01:32:42,200
work in a deep and undisturbed way. And 
then Start At The End by Matt Waller,  

1125
01:32:42,200 --> 01:32:45,800
who's a behavioral scientist buddy 
of mine. Really thoughtful book,  

1126
01:32:45,800 --> 01:32:49,760
helps you really think about what you're 
